Glendale.Cahuenga, California:
Cahuenga (also, Cabeugna and Cabuenga) or "place of the hill" is a former Tongva and Tataviam (Fernandeño - Gabrieleño) Native American settlement in the San Fernando Valley of Los Angeles, Los Angeles County, California.
Its precise location is unknown.
The name was used for the historic Mexican land grant Rancho Cahuenga.
